To determine how much a metal rod will expand when heated by an additional $25^\circ$C, we can use the concept of thermal expansion. The linear expansion of a material is often described by the formula:

$$
\begin{equation*}
    \Delta L = \alpha L_0 \Delta T \, ,
\end{equation*}
$$

where:
- $\Delta L$ is the change in length (expansion);
